==Introduction==
A '''Banner Layout''' renders group of components using the following rules:
* there are four distinctive areas in the box: left, center, right and bottom
* definition of the layout allows to define which properties/widgets shall be displayed in each of the areas

Usually left and right areas are used to display related icons (with links to other related concepts),
center area displays title (subject) of the page, and bottom area displays some complimentary information.

The banner layout is applicable only on the view pages. On the edit pages table is automatically used.

==Definition==
<pre>
<concept>
  <structure>
    <group name="1"  layout="banner" bannerLeft="{LEFT COMPONENTS}" bannerCenter="{CENTER COMPONENTS}" bannerRight="{RIGHT COMPONENTS}" bannerBottom="{BOTTOM COMPONENTS}">
      <property name="Property A.1.a">
      <property name="Property A.1.b">
      <property name="Property A.1.c">
    </group>
  </structure>
</concept>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {LEFT COMPONENTS}
| A list of properties/widgets to be displayed in the left area of the banner
|-
! {RIGHT COMPONENTS}
| A list of properties/widgets to be displayed in the right area of the banner
|-
! {CENTER COMPONENTS}
| A list of properties/widgets to be displayed in the center area of the banner. If not specified a name of the page is displayed.
|-
! {BOTTOM COMPONENTS}
| A list of properties/widgets to be displayed in the bottom area of the banner
|}


==Example==
<pre>
<concept name="Focus Area" >
  <structure>
    <group name="Top">
      <group name="Focus Area" layout="banner" bannerLeft="Image" bannerRight="Is part of">
        <property name="Is part of" mandatory="true" refersTo="Exercise" label="Exercise" attribute="exercise" stereotype="composition" multiplicity="one" format="gallery"/>
        </property>
        <property name="Image" mandatory="true" width="75"/>
        <property name="Title" mandatory="true"/>
      </group>
  </structure>
</concept>
</pre>


